of the Cathedra Petri according to Curial Ceremony. The second discourse concerns, on the other hand, a description of the basilica of Santa Maria Maggiore on the Esquiline Hill, which Sirleto composed for the Cardinal Bishop of Milan, Carlo Borromeo. In contrast to the edition of the first discourse in this volume, the Trattato sopra la chiesa di Santa Maria Maggiore is presented according to the correspondence between Borromeo and Sirleto.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aGuglielmo Sirleto. 4aPapsttum. 4aRömische Kurie. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aEarly modern period.  aGuglielmo Sirleto.  aRoman curia.  apapacy.1 aMalesevic, Filip, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfondsefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG0 cprintz978311076549640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110765519zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110765519zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110765519/original  a978-3-11-117578-2 DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3